# Summary and Keywords

**Summary:** This documentation explains how Amplitude Experiment estimates experiment duration to achieve statistical significance, detailing how the feature works, why estimates might not appear, the meaning of best/average/worst case scenarios, and potential errors in the estimation process. The feature is only available for primary metrics and sequential testing.

**Keywords:**
- experiment duration estimation
- statistical significance
- best/average/worst case scenarios
- exposure calculation
- estimation errors
- irreducible errors
- drift errors
- 40-day estimation cap
- sequential testing
- hypothesis testing
- confidence intervals
- variance calculation